project_descr: Global Fund HIV grant (2016-2017) managed by UNDP Angola Country Office as Principal Recipient. The grant aims to contribute to achieving national targets in the response to HIV, as outlined in the National Strategic Plan (2015-2018).

outputs.output_descr: By 2018, the Grant aims to expand access to the following services : HIV prevention for key populations; Prevention of Mother-to-Child Transmission of HIV; HIV antiretroviral treatment ; and diagnosis and treatment of HIV/TB co-infection.
donor_name: UNITED NATIONS DEVELOPMENT FUND FOR WOME
GLOBAL FUND TO FIGHT AIDS, TUBERCULOSIS

project_title: strengthening the national response to hiv in angola
